{
  "doc_id": "53126",
  "text": "Creating fluidic connections between microfluidic devices and the outside world represents a challenge. Contributing to this are a lack of standards for interconnecting components and a difference of scale [CITATION_1] . Terms such as 'macro-tomicro' and 'world-to-chip' reflect the scale disparity between typical microfluidic channel dimensions, microns to hundreds of microns, and the tool and methods (often by hand) used to connect these to the outside world [CITATION_2] . Additionally, the cost associated with packaging or interfacing devices can be prohibitive [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
